summary:
Collins Muambo is an International Development Specialist with focus on Conflict Management, Reconciliation and Social Cohesion. He holds two Masters Degree in Governance and International Relations from the the Institute of Development Policy Belgium and the International Relations Institute of Cameroon. Prior to that, he end a Bachelor's Degree in History and Political Science and currently serves as a Civil Affairs Officer with the United Nations Mission in South Sudan.

He is proactive and confident with the ability to work efficiently as a team and independently too.
